    "visualization_explanation": "The visualization employs a 1D categorical dataset with six atmospheric layers as ordinal variables. Synthetic equal-weight values (all 1) create proportional stacking, while custom metadata encodes layer heights and characteristics. Data quality is conceptual rather than quantitative, prioritizing structural relationships over precise measurements. The column chart maximizes data-ink ratio by eliminating axes and gridlines, focusing attention on the proportional relationships between layers. Cairo's principles of salience are implemented through high-contrast black labels on white columns, while the stacking order follows natural atmospheric stratification. Uniform segment widths maintain Tufte's principle of proportional integrity, with text annotations providing concrete scale references despite the normalized percentage presentation."
